-- Tottenham’s Dawson May Join Southampton or QPR: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-10-23T10:08:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-23/tottenham-s-dawson-may-join-southampton-or-qpr-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the web.  Dawson Move?  Southampton wants to sign Tottenham center-half  Michael
Dawson , who is free to leave White Hart Lane in the January
transfer window, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Dawson, 28, remains a target for Queens Park Rangers, which
sought to hire him in the offseason, the Mirror said.  Huntelaar Bid  Liverpool will try to hire Schalke striker Klaas-Jan
Huntelaar in January, the  Daily Star  reported.  Huntelaar, 29, has postponed talks to renew his contract
with the Bundesliga team until December and could leave if they
are unsuccessful, according to the Star.  De Gea Exit?  Real  Madrid  is eyeing Manchester United’s Spanish
goalkeeper David de Gea as a future replacement for  Iker Casillas , the  Daily Mail  reported.  De Gea is sharing goalkeeping duties with Anders Lindegaard
at United this season, the Mail said.  Souness May Return  Former Liverpool coach Graeme Souness could return to
coaching after six years away to lead Bolton in the
Championship, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Souness is on a shortlist of candidates along with Crystal
Palace’s Dougie Freedman and former Wolves manager  Mick McCarthy , the Mirror said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
